      "span_text": "Hence, the distribution in the gall bladder and small intestine is therefore likely explained by the size of individual radiolabeled GVs and/or cluster of radiolabeled GVs and of the presence of fragmented [ 99m Tc]GVs that are all compounds too large to be cleared by the kidneys [CITATION_1] ."
